There  seems  to be a little confusion here.  The NIC is going to
be maintaining the host.txt file for the DDN (as  they  currently
are  doing).   This  file will have to include all hosts that DDN
hosts that do not implement name server system are interested in.
This is independent of how the hosts are named.  All hosts on the
Aarpanet side of the sytem will be implementing the  name  domain
system.

Thus,  no  mail  relays  are  needed,  but the NIC has to do some
things to make sure that the DDN community does not lose too much
of its desired connectivity with the rest of the internet.

Hope this clarifies at least this small part of the problem.

Barry

